{
  "stem": "24814.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "People's lungs would just fill up with blood, and there wasn't anything we could do about it except keep them comfortable.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "The gastrointestinal type was particularly horrible to take care of as you can imagine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Blood coming out both ends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And sometimes it attacks the central nervous system.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "I wrote about that in my book.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "The spine-- the brain cord-- the spinal cord and brain.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And this one pathetic case I'll remember to my dying day, this man had typhus of the spinal cord and brain, and he was convulsing, like a man with lockjaw.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And he drew himself up in a bow, so that just his heels and the back of his head touched the bed.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "The rest of his body was just taut, like that, screaming at the top of his lungs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Then he fell dead, wham, just while we looked at him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The death rate was so high that we always knew, as we went along each row of beds, which was, say, 40-some, as I recall, some would be dead that we'd passed that had been alive when we went by.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "It was incredibly high.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] The stories, of course, were endless.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "I was picked up because I was a Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "It was very common.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "And I've been worked here and worked there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "And the stories-- the second-hand stories I heard of the beatings and shootings and the casual murders were blood curdling, and I guess you've heard plenty of stories like that.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, one of-- the one man told me about being in one of those railway boxcars, when they locked-- you know, they slammed people in a boxcar so tightly they couldn't breathe.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
